-- Cemex to Asist Mexico Clean-Energy Fund, Invest in Power Plants
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-10-30T18:49:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-30/cemex-to-asist-mexico-clean-energy-fund-invest-in-power-plants.html
Cemex SAB, the largest cement maker
in the Americas, will provide technical assistance to a fund
that’s seeking to raise $300 million to build clean-energy
projects in  Mexico .  Cemex may take equity stakes of as much as 10 percent in
specific projects, the Monterrey, Mexico-based company said
today in a statement. Cemex didn’t identify the fund, which is
planning to offer capital development certificates on the
Mexican stock exchange  To contact the reporter on this story:
